  "instructions": [
    "Heat claypot over medium heat.",
    "Add beef chuck and cook until browned, breaking it up into small pieces as it cooks.",
    "Add onion, garlic, carrots, and potatoes, and cook until vegetables are tender.",
    "Add smoked paprika, harissa, cumin, salt, and black pepper, and stir to combine.",
    "Pour in red wine vinegar and beef broth, and add water to cover the ingredients.",
    "Bring mixture to a boil, then reduce heat to low and simmer for 1.5 hours, or until beef is tender.",
    "Season with additional salt and pepper to taste.",
    "Garnish with parsley and serve hot."
